Celine's Billboard gown was filled with tissues: Stylist.
Singer Celine Dion's sleeves on the gown she adorned for the Billboard Music Awards this year were packed with tissue paper, according to her stylist, Law Roach.Dion, 49, flaunted a floor-length, figure-hugging, white gown with a v-plunge neckline and accentuated shoulder details to the awards gala on May 21.Roach has now revealed that the garment was shipped in a "huge box" while the arm area was stuffed with wadding to protect it."It came in a huge box. The sleeves were packed up with tissue paper -- it's a whole thing, for real," Roach told hollywoodreporter.com.